PROJECT OVERVIEW
HealthConnect is a Hospital Management System (HMS) designed specifically for the Pediatrics Department of QSUT
(Qendra Spitalore Universitare "Nënë Tereza"), the largest public hospital in Albania, located in Tirana.
The system aims to digitize and streamline the department's daily operations — from patient registration 
and bed management to doctor assignments and discharge summaries — replacing outdated paper-based workflows with an integrated, 
reliable digital platform.

Problem Statement
The Pediatrics Department at QSUT currently faces several operational challenges: 
manual patient registration leads to data duplication and errors, there is no centralized tracking of bed availability and ward occupancy,
paper-based medical records make it difficult to access patient history quickly, poor coordination exists between doctors, nurses, 
and administrative staff, there is a lack of reporting tools to monitor department performance, and long waiting times occur due 
to unstructured appointment and triage processes. HealthConnect addresses these problems 
by providing a unified digital system tailored to the specific workflows of a public pediatric hospital department in Albania.


System Features and Users
The HealthConnect system is designed to improve the management of the Pediatrics Department at Qendra Spitalore Universitare "Nënë Tereza" by 
digitizing patient and hospital operations. The main users of the system are Administrators, Doctors, Nurses, Receptionists and Users. 
Administrators manage the system and user accounts, doctors update medical records and treatments, nurses assist with 
patient information and bed monitoring, and receptionists handle patient registration and scheduling. The system includes key features 
such as patient registration, bed management, doctor assignment, medical records management, and discharge summaries, 
helping the hospital replace paper-based processes with a more efficient digital system.
